node.text: Just v grateful today💕 but full transparency-for the last few weeks, I’ve been having days of debilitating anxiety. No rhyme or reason. I wake up in my beautiful home with my precious dog, love what I do, surrounded by incredible, supportive friends. Yet still feel unmotivated and in a fog almost. I don’t want to talk to anyone or leave my house (more so than unusual🙃) It’s hard for me to verbalize how I feel on those days because it makes no sense, even to me. So then I feel guilty for feeling that way! I have too much to be thankful for to feel like this?! It’s a bizarre little cycle this anxiety thing, but it helps me to know I’m not alone in those feelings. I’m not sure where I was going with this bc I can’t focus long enough to finish a thought, but just wanted you to know you’re not alone either. Thankful for my IG fam& for good days like today💖 LOVE YA MEAN IT!

node.text:
Over the next few weeks social media will be full of Father’s Day posts so I wanted to share mine a little early in honor of my Dad’s report from his oncologist😊 in cased you missed my story, my dad found out his stage 4 colon cancer is shrinking in multiple places!! Praise JESUS🙌🏼 I feel so lucky to be this guy’s baby girl. He’s treated me like a princess and held me to the highest standard since birth. My goal in life is to make him& my mama proud and I believe I’ve done so. I’ve gotten thousands of messages from y’all sharing stories of family members battling cancer& stories of loss from cancer, (lots of daddies too), and the number one theme is “cherish your time”. I hate that this God awful diagnosis is what made me realize how precious time is, but I’ll never take a text, conversation, or moment for granted again. My heart is with all of you who may be struggling with this upcoming day. Happy Father’s Day to you, Papa Bear!! Looking forward to the next 50 of em! I love you to the moon! 

#fuckcancer
